# Legacy API (reference only)

Applies when old PHP API code exists (e.g. on `main`, a tag, or `legacy/` snapshot).

## Allowed

- Read old handlers to learn **behavior** for Pest parity tests
- Copy **test fixtures** and OpenAPI examples
- One-line comments pointing to old route for auditors

## Forbidden

- New endpoints or features in legacy `MailApi`, `*Kernel`, `ApiDomainHandlers`, etc.
- “Delegate to legacy” in new Laravel services
- Moving legacy files into `app/` without rewriting them
- Extracting “shared” static PDO helpers for new code to call
- Copying `Paths::data().'/files'` or Sabre `FS\Directory` patterns into new code instead of Flysystem

New work lives only in greenfield structure (`Http/Controllers`, `Services`, `Models`, `Storage`, Form Requests). Delete reference code from the new branch as each domain is ported and tests pass.
